ADI

Amount and duration of interruptions

Mnemonic: ADI

Category: Testing team

Description: The amount and length of work interruptions in each project, motivated by tasks related to other projects, breaks for meals, rest, and vacations, as well as waiting for the availability of information or artifact by the development team.

Impact: Positive

Rationale: When a task is interrupted, depending on the interruption time, it may be necessary to apply effort to remember at what point the work was stopped and which solution was being applied.
